records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody on WRIT.
State moves to dismiss both enhancers.  Motion granted.
GUILTY plea entered to the amended charge of deliver Suboxone.  Convicted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend ninety (90) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing immediately;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
5) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) provide DNA sample;
9) obtain high school diploma, GED or HSED.
$500.00 cash bail is ordered applied to court costs.
Minutes.
